  "name": "Morrison COU2 — VAD hemolysis credibility assessment (W-AL-02 sensitivity gap)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under ventricular assist device (VAD) conditions. COU2 evaluates whether the computational model can predict absolute hemolysis levels for a Class III VAD device at Model Risk Level 5. Monte Carlo uncertainty quantification is performed across all five flow-speed operating points; a screening sensitivity study was conducted during model development and is discussed in the UQ narrative, confirming that inlet flow rate and impeller rotational speed are the primary drivers of predicted hemolysis index variance. All 13 credibility factors have been assessed and required levels are met or exceeded. Decision: Accepted.",
