      "acceptanceCriteria": "All model input parameters must be characterized with probability distributions and propagated through Monte Carlo UQ; dominant input drivers identified through sensitivity screening.",
      "rationale": "Twelve input parameters assigned probability distributions based on manufacturer tolerances and literature: inlet flow rate (±5%), rotational speed (±2%), blood viscosity (±8%), hematocrit (±3%), and eight geometric tolerances. All twelve propagated through 5000-sample Monte Carlo simulation. A screening sensitivity study is described in UQ report section 4.2, identifying inlet flow rate and rotational speed as primary variance drivers. Input characterization at achieved level 4 meets required level 4."
