    "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/decision/vad-hemolysis-decision-001",
    "type": "DecisionRecord",
    "actor": "https://uofa.net/synth/actor/morrison-credibility-assessment-team",
    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "All 13 credibility factors assessed; required levels met or exceeded across all factors. Monte Carlo uncertainty quantification performed with 5000 samples propagating 12 input parameter distributions. UQ prediction intervals bracket experimental observations at 4 of 5 operating points. A screening sensitivity study discussed in the UQ report confirms that inlet flow rate and rotational speed are the dominant variance contributors to predicted hemolysis index. Model form uncertainty included in UQ. Discretization error characterized below 5% GCI. Independent peer review completed without findings. Overall credibility sufficient to support regulatory submission for Class III VAD hemolysis acceptance at MRL 5.",
